Paul Okoye aka Rudeboy of PSquare has taken a shot with presidential aspirant of the Labour Party (LP), Peter Obi ahead of the 2023 general elections. The singer, in a recent Instagram post, declared his support for the former People’s Democratic Party (PDP) vice presidential aspirant, who ditched the party for the Labour Party on May 27. Kingrudy appealed to Nigerians to get their PVC (Permanent Voter’s Card).   Comedian Funny bone gets engaged     Dollar heading to N1,000, Davido cries out     How Nigerian men define strong women, by Toke Makinwa   Read Also: BREAKING: Peter Obi secures Labour Party presidential ticket Sharing the photo, he wrote: “My fellow Nigerians pls get your PVC… If we miss this opportunity is another 8 years of backwardness till 2031. #Obidiently.” Commenting under the post, Peter Okoye aka Mr P practically patted his twin brother on the back, seeking support for Obi. “Pls can somebody give him a chilled bottle beer. Dear Nigerians and the Youths! This is not about the North or South here. We are no longer interested in party politics but the qualities of the candidate! If we miss this opportunity! We might never get it again. #PeterObi2023,” he wrote.